usage: check_humanize_invariants.py [-h] [--format {auto,markdown,tex}]
                                    [--json] [--allow-quote-edits]
                                    [--strict-speech-acts] [--fragment]
                                    [--term TERM]
                                    before after

Check preservation invariants between original and humanized Markdown/TeX.

positional arguments:
  before                Original UTF-8 Markdown or TeX file
  after                 Humanized UTF-8 Markdown or TeX file

options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --format {auto,markdown,tex}
  --json                Emit machine-readable JSON
  --allow-quote-edits   Do not protect direct quotations (off by default)
  --strict-speech-acts  Treat changes to
                        negation/modality/focus/definition/reporting markers
                        as hard errors
  --fragment            Validate a document fragment: unchanged boundary
                        imbalance is allowed, but any environment or brace-
                        balance drift still fails
  --term TERM           Protect an exact method, material, or glossary term;
                        repeat for multiple terms
